                                <h3 class="small-title"><a href="#">History and Culture</a></h3>
                                <p>
                                    Cabo San Lucas (Spanish pronunciation: ['kaßo san 'lukas] Cape Saint Luke), commonly called Cabo in American English, is a city at the southern tip of the Baja California Peninsula, in the Mexican state of Baja California Sur. Cabo San Lucas together with San José del Cabo is known as Los Cabos. </p>
                                <p>Cabo has been rated as one of Mexico's top 5 tourist destinations, popular for its beaches, scuba diving locations, the arch (Arco de Cabo San Lucas), and marine life. The Los Cabos Corridor has become a heavily trafficked holiday destination for tourists, with numerous resorts and timeshares along the coast between Cabo San Lucas and San José del Cabo.</p>
                            </div>

